Class PolarityModifier_Type

  • java.lang.Object
    • Annotation_Type
      • org.apache.ctakes.typesystem.type.textsem.IdentifiedAnnotation_Type

          • org.apache.ctakes.typesystem.type.textsem.PolarityModifier_Type

  • public class PolarityModifier_Type
extends Modifier_Type
    Used to indicate that a procedure or assertion did not occur or does not exist. If indicated, negation is present and polarity should be -1. If not indicated, negation is not present and polarity should be +1 by default. Updated by JCasGen Wed Sep 30 11:06:15 EDT 2015
